      • toJavaDefinition

        public String toJavaDefinition(String prefix,
                               boolean generateAnnotations)
        Outputs a Java definition for the property, including a comment if there is a comment for the property. The comment will be formatted slightly differently if it's very long. If generateAnnotations is true, then a Predicate annotation will be generated for each declaration containing the URI of the property. DataType properties will be encoded as Strings and Object properties will be declared as their appropriate type.
        Parameters:
        prefix - The String prefix to add to all lines in the generated code
        generateAnnotations - Whether to generate @@Predicate annotations
        Returns:
        A string containing a Java definition
